Main Components of docker-compose.yml
Keyword	Purpose
version	Compose file version (optional in newer Compose)
services	Defines containers
image	Docker image to use
build	Build image from Dockerfile
ports	Port mapping
volumes	Persistent storage
networks	Container networking
environment	Environment variables
depends_on	Service startup dependency
restart	Restart policy
Simple Example
services:

  nginx:
    image: nginx
    ports:
      - "8080:80"

Run:

docker compose up

Stop:

docker compose down
Multi-Container Example

Suppose we have:

Web Application

Frontend
     |
Backend
     |
MySQL
docker-compose.yml
version: "3.9"

services:

  mysql:
    image: mysql:8
    container_name: mysql-db
    restart: always
    environment:
      MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD: root123
      MYSQL_DATABASE: mydb
    volumes:
      - mysql-data:/var/lib/mysql

  backend:
    image: my-backend:latest
    container_name: backend
    restart: always
    ports:
      - "5000:5000"
    depends_on:
      - mysql

  frontend:
    image: nginx
    container_name: frontend
    ports:
      - "8080:80"
    depends_on:
      - backend

volumes:
  mysql-data:
Explanation
services

Defines all containers.

services:
image

Specifies the image to use.

image: nginx

Equivalent to:

docker run nginx
container_name
container_name: frontend

Instead of a random container name, Docker uses frontend.

ports
ports:
  - "8080:80"

Meaning:

Host 8080
     |
Container 80

Open:

http://localhost:8080
environment
environment:
  MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD: root123

Equivalent to:

docker run -e MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=root123 mysql
volumes
volumes:
  - mysql-data:/var/lib/mysql
mysql-data → Docker volume
/var/lib/mysql → Container path

Ensures database data persists after container recreation.

depends_on
depends_on:
  - mysql

The backend starts after Docker starts the MySQL container.

Note: depends_on controls startup order only. It does not wait until MySQL is ready to accept connections.

restart
restart: always

Restart policies:

restart: no
restart: on-failure
restart: unless-stopped
restart: always
Build Instead of Image

Instead of downloading an image:

services:
  app:
    build: .

Docker builds the image using the Dockerfile in the current directory.

Build from Another Directory
services:
  app:
    build:
      context: .
      dockerfile: Dockerfile
